<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <link href="styles.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body>
<div class="canvas-app">
    <img src="nodejs.png"/>
    <p>Hello, <%= user.firstName %>. This is a web app written in Node.js embedded in your Salesforce page (It could also be written in any other language).</p>
    <p>It is aware of its environment. For example, here are a few things it knows:</p>
    <table>
        <tr><td>User:</td><td><%= user.fullName %></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Object:</td><td><%= environment.record.attributes.type %></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Id:</td><td><%= environment.record.Id %></td></tr>
    </table>
    <p>It can also access Salesforce data using the REST APIs. With context and APIs, it's easy to integrate applications written in any language inside your Salesforce pages.</p>
</div>
</body>
